events.description: The release of Indonesia's gross domestic product data for the fourth quarter of 2025, showing a 5.39% year-on-year increase.
Natural disasters that occurred in three Indonesian provinces, impacting the full-year economic growth.

facts.fact_text: Indonesia’s GDP advanced 5.39% yoy in Q4 2025, surpassing market expectations of 5.01%.

evidences.evidence_text: Indonesia’s GDP advanced 5.39% yoy in Q4 2025, accelerating from 5.04% in Q3 and surpassing market expectations of 5.01%.

facts.fact_text: For the full year 2025, Indonesia's GDP rose 5.11%, which was below the government’s 5.2% target.

evidences.evidence_text: For the full year, GDP rose 5.11%, below the government’s 5.2% target

facts.fact_text: Private consumption grew by 5.11% in Q4 2025 compared to 4.89% in Q3.

evidences.evidence_text: boosted by solid private consumption (5.11% vs 4.89% in Q3)

facts.fact_text: Fixed investment growth increased to 6.12% in Q4 from 5.04% in Q3.

evidences.evidence_text: Also, fixed investment gained traction (6.12% vs 5.04%).

claims.claim_text: The Indonesian economy is expected to grow by 5.4% in 2026.

evidences.evidence_text: For 2026, the economy is expected to grow by 5.4%.

claims.claim_text: The failure to meet the annual GDP target was a reflection of the impact of natural disasters in three provinces.

evidences.evidence_text: reflecting the impact of natural disasters in three provinces, though still the strongest annual growth in three years.

evidence.evidence_text: boosted by solid private consumption... amid continued government support measures and lower borrowing costs
reflecting the impact of natural disasters in three provinces
It was the strongest yearly growth since Q3 2022, boosted by solid private consumption
Also, fixed investment gained traction (6.12% vs 5.04%).
